Introduction: Chief People Officer

Cornerstone #4 - Chief People Officer

Welcome to the Cornerstone Project: Chief People Officer!

By now, you've already seen the entire machine learning workflow from start to finish. You've practiced exploring a dataset, cleaning it, engineering new features, recruiting appropriate algorithms, and efficiently building a kick-ass model using cross-validation.

Now it's time to really solidify those concepts. Now, you'll step into the driver's seat and build another great machine learning model... this time for a classification task. That means we'll provide less formal guidance, although we'll still introduce several new concepts. After completing this project, you'll be comfortable navigating the entire applied machine learning workflow on your own.

So watch the brief intro video above, and then we'll see you in the next module... Exploratory Analysis Plus: Chasing Aha! Moments.

IMPORTANT: You can find the project bundle in the downloads section. It will have relevant companion workbooks and/or worksheets for each module. After watching the module video, complete the coding section by following along in your workbook (if applicable) and the exercises or worksheet.
